1
00:00:09,279 --> 00:00:13,160
[narrator] For 6,000 years, man has
accepted the finality of physical death,

2
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:16,679
and when it comes,
he goes to a familiar grave.

3
00:00:17,879 --> 00:00:21,640
But today, for those who see
the prospect of immortality,

4
00:00:21,719 --> 00:00:24,039
there's a new
and less permanent resting place.

5
00:00:24,559 --> 00:00:26,679
The start of a silent revolution

6
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,879
which could affect
the future of the world.

7
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:34,679
In those capsules,
people who determine to live twice,

8
00:00:34,759 --> 00:00:37,560
who prefer the freezer to the grave.

9
00:00:38,119 --> 00:00:41,399
The first of the
"die now, live later" group.

10
00:00:41,479 --> 00:00:44,079
Men and women
frozen solid in their cylinders,

11
00:00:44,159 --> 00:00:45,359
waiting for the future.

12
00:00:45,479 --> 00:00:47,079
[metal scraping]

13
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:52,200
And, they believe, cheating death.

14
00:01:01,799 --> 00:01:05,480
[announcer 1] Person placed in cryonic
suspension is probably...

15
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:08,280
without a doubt, it's the most sanitary,
and most scientific,

16
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:11,719
and perfect form of preservation
we can possibly imagine.

17
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,599
[announcer 2]
Each individual on this planet

18
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,920
has one big overriding problem,

19
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,200
his own death.

20
00:01:19,719 --> 00:01:22,319
And it's a big problem
and no one has solved it yet.

21
00:01:51,439 --> 00:01:55,280
[Sahatorn in Thai] It was morning when we
discovered the aquarium's oxygen pump,

22
00:01:55,359 --> 00:02:00,640
which supplied air to the aquarium,
had broken overnight.

23
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:10,039
Our mother announced,
"No school today. Save the goldfish!"

24
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,800
So we scooped out the floating fish

25
00:02:19,879 --> 00:02:22,520
and put them in an ice bath.

26
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:30,759
Lowering their temperature
slowed down the death process.

27
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:41,719
And we found we could revive them later.

28
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:52,479
We were very successful.

29
00:02:53,759 --> 00:02:59,360
More than 50% were revived.

30
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,759
[Nareerat] Come on. Let's go!

31
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,080
-Beep, beep.
-[Nareerat] Beep, beep!

32
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,080
Daddy.

33
00:03:38,479 --> 00:03:40,039
[both chuckle]

34
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:46,840
We named our daughter Einz.

35
00:03:46,919 --> 00:03:51,159
In Japanese and Chinese,
"Einz" means "love."

36
00:03:51,759 --> 00:03:54,400
-[Sahatorn] What kind of bed is this?
-My sister's crib.

37
00:03:55,599 --> 00:03:56,719
[Sahatorn] Yeah.

38
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,639
Are you doing this for your sister?
Or are you just following my orders?

39
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,560
For my sister!

40
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,599
-Do you really love your sister?
-Yes, really.

41
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,080
-Do you really want a sister?
-I haven't even met her yet.

42
00:04:08,159 --> 00:04:10,000
-Do you really want her?
-Yes, I do.

43
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:14,039
If she watches this video later,
what would you like to tell her?

44
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:16,199
I love you, little sister.

45
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,199
-Hmm?
-I love you, little sister.

46
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:23,199
[Sahatorn] Einz was born out of
Matrix's wish for a sibling.

47
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:29,000
[Matrix] Hello. Today is March 2nd, 2012.

48
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:31,319
I've brought my sister to the mall.

49
00:04:31,399 --> 00:04:33,839
It's the first time she's left the house.

50
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,160
[Sahatorn] He was an only child then.

51
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,959
[Matrix in English] When she was born...

52
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:49,000
I drew a little house, and a door,
and a countdown...

53
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:56,360
saying that,
"29 days until Einz arrives." [chuckles]

54
00:04:56,439 --> 00:05:00,839
And I changed the date every day,
30, 29...

55
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,759
until...

56
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:08,120
until, uh, the day she was born.

57
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:11,480
I think I cried.

58
00:05:12,319 --> 00:05:13,879
I was so happy.

59
00:05:13,959 --> 00:05:16,959
[Nareerat in Thai] Why are you sitting
on the chair by yourself?

60
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,680
Such a gifted child you are!

61
00:05:18,759 --> 00:05:20,279
[Nareerat chuckles]

62
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,240
One, two, three!

63
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:40,519
[Sahatorn] Einz brought

64
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,920
the whole family together.

65
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:48,040
Everyone had been waiting for her.

66
00:05:50,399 --> 00:05:52,079
[woman] Here she comes!

67
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:59,040
[Nareerat] Daddy! Daddy! You're 40 now!

68
00:05:59,879 --> 00:06:02,040
Today is Daddy's birthday.

69
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,920
And you have your new daughter with you.

70
00:06:05,839 --> 00:06:09,600
[Nareerat] Our family today
includes my husband,

71
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:12,800
Dr. Sahatorn, nicknamed "Top."

72
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:17,720
Then there's our eldest son, Matrix

73
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:21,439
and our daughter Matheryn, or Einz.

74
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:25,360
[Nareerat] Such a pretty dress.

75
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:29,120
[Sahatorn] My little Einz.

76
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:02,560
I think that for the bottom bit,
just drill a little and put this in there.

77
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:05,399
For the upper bit,
we'll clamp it until it's flush.

78
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:09,040
Just a little effort, and it should fuse.

79
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,800
In our family...

80
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:22,959
we place a lot of importance on science.

81
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:27,560
That means,
if we know something, we say we know.

82
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:30,920
If we do not know something,
we say we do not know.

83
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,360
Just because we don't know something,
it doesn't mean it's not true.

84
00:07:38,839 --> 00:07:43,639
My family knows that I always used

85
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:46,800
the scientific way of thinking
to solve problems.

86
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:53,120
[Nareerat] We have
a good head of the family.

87
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:56,160
I was once Sahatorn's student.

88
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,920
He is still my teacher.

89
00:08:02,279 --> 00:08:05,759
A teacher for our children.

90
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:23,920
[Matrix in English] What I like
about science is that

91
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,800
most of the thing can be explained.

92
00:08:30,399 --> 00:08:33,799
Everything is natural and unnatural
at the same time.

93
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:37,480
[professor] Just grab a pair of goggles.

94
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:43,000
We're talking about thermal physics,
which is all about particles, of course.

95
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:45,759
So, if you were able to see
those particles,

96
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:48,360
what would be different about them
as I'm heating it?

97
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:53,559
It would be vibrating at a frequency
of a certain color of the light.

98
00:08:53,639 --> 00:08:57,360
[professor] Okay. You're absolutely right.
The frequency of the light.

99
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,679
[in Thai] This.

100
00:08:59,759 --> 00:09:01,639
Haven't used this in a while.

101
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,639
[Matrix in English] When people talk
about my sister, they'll be like...

102
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:11,799
"Oh, I'm so sorry. But it's okay
if you don't wanna talk about it."

103
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,159
But...

104
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,159
I...

105
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:17,039
I don't want to forget...

106
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,960
the pain we've been through together.
I don't want to...

107
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,399
leave out the bad memories.

108
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:30,120
They're all memories
and I feel like I wanna keep all of them.

109
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,679
I don't wanna...
I don't want to ever forget them.

110
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,519
[Sahatorn in Thai] What happened was...

111
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:44,759
We were working on a project
in another province.

112
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:49,759
Matrix, being in Bangkok,
was the one taking care of his sister.

113
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:57,320
I had this bad feeling. A nightmare.

114
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:06,120
So I phoned Matrix in the morning
and told him to go and wake Einz up.

115
00:10:08,039 --> 00:10:10,000
But he couldn't wake her up.

116
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:14,240
[siren wailing]

117
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:30,799
[Nareerat] On that day, our daughter went
into a coma and was unable to wake up.

118
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:34,519
[Nareerat singing softly]

119
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:40,279
I wished I could take her place.

120
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:44,559
Take her pain away. Be the one who's sick.

121
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:47,240
I've always felt
nothing could happen to her

122
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:49,440
because her mother is here to protect her.

123
00:10:49,519 --> 00:10:52,200
It's gonna be okay, honey. It's okay.
It's gonna be okay.

124
00:11:05,679 --> 00:11:10,759
[Sahatorn] The neurosurgeon said
it is probably ependymoblastoma.

125
00:11:14,279 --> 00:11:15,720
No one had ever survived it.

126
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:22,080
[Nareerat] Einz has the deadliest
brain cancer in the world.

127
00:11:30,679 --> 00:11:36,240
Since the day she fell into a coma,
Einz underwent ten surgeries,

128
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:39,440
twelve rounds of chemo,
and 20 rounds of radiation.

129
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:45,120
She was in and out of comas.
Always in and out of the ICU and PICU.

130
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:57,799
But through it all,
she always woke with a smile.

131
00:11:57,879 --> 00:12:00,080
Everyone waited for Einz's smile.

132
00:12:00,879 --> 00:12:04,480
-[woman] Here comes Ei-Ei!
-[Sahatorn] Here comes Ei-Ei!

133
00:12:05,039 --> 00:12:06,240
[woman] Yay!

134
00:12:06,919 --> 00:12:08,639
[kissing]

135
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:18,120
[Sahatorn] My heart was rebelling.
Maybe there was a chance.

136
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,879
So we had to keep fighting
until we were sure there was no chance.

137
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:33,799
I didn't have the right to decide.

138
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:39,559
She did. She had the right to decide
whether she would keep fighting.

139
00:12:56,000 --> 00:13:00,559
[Nareerat] I discovered
that my husband had this powerful love.

140
00:13:01,279 --> 00:13:07,200
Throughout 100 days of illness,
he never got a full night's sleep,

141
00:13:07,279 --> 00:13:13,080
because he was researching
the latest technology and treatments.

142
00:13:18,159 --> 00:13:24,440
[Sahatorn] I've started collecting
her cancer cells from surgery to culture.

143
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:31,000
But I'm not an expert in this field
so I've experienced many obstacles.

144
00:13:31,639 --> 00:13:34,519
But what's important
is that I don't give up.

145
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:40,759
Even if the chances of success are low,
I have to keep working on it.

146
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:54,600
[Matrix in English] My dad spent
nearly every day,

147
00:13:54,679 --> 00:14:01,000
when my sister was sick,
at Chula to, um, test medicines...

148
00:14:01,559 --> 00:14:03,200
on her cancer cells.

149
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:09,919
I personally think he's
one of the mad scientists.

150
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:16,320
But many things in the world
that have been invented...

151
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:20,600
were invented by mad scientists

152
00:14:20,679 --> 00:14:25,120
because they were crazy enough
to think of something new.

153
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:33,360
[Sahatorn in Thai] I experimented
with around five kinds of chemicals

154
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,559
as well as other treatments

155
00:14:35,639 --> 00:14:38,840
that had the possibility
of curing my baby.

156
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:40,200
You mean...

157
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:46,759
you will place this camera here
to observe the cell culture.

158
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:51,799
Yes, to see if the cells are normal.

159
00:14:51,879 --> 00:14:56,679
Then when we're done,
we prepare the tissues here.

160
00:14:56,759 --> 00:15:02,360
After that, we bring the different cells
to the hypoxia closet.

161
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:10,039
[Sahatorn] There's so much
suffering in life.

162
00:15:11,039 --> 00:15:15,600
We are under so much pressure
as we fight this.

163
00:15:15,679 --> 00:15:20,120
As scientists, we know the chances

164
00:15:20,679 --> 00:15:25,799
of finding the right medicine in time
are slim.

165
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:40,039
I began to think,
what if the doctors can't find a cure?

166
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,399
Can't find a way. What should we do?

167
00:15:43,879 --> 00:15:47,720
That's when cryonics entered my mind.

168
00:15:47,799 --> 00:15:50,240
[narrator in English] It's a possibility
that's existed

169
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,799
in science fiction for years.

170
00:15:51,879 --> 00:15:55,919
Two American corporations
now claim to offer it as a reality...

171
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,960
[man] It sounds like science fiction
but it's not.

172
00:15:58,039 --> 00:15:59,639
[woman 1] I wanna live until tomorrow.

173
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,360
I wanna live forever and ever.
I love life.

174
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:05,279
-[woman 2] I wanna see the future.
-Death is an option.

175
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:07,440
The idea of reanimating
is wishful thinking.

176
00:16:07,519 --> 00:16:10,240
I don't care if it's robotic.
I don't care what my body is.

177
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:15,360
[Sahatorn in Thai] I've always loved
this area of science since I was a kid.

178
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:19,279
I've always known what cryonics was.

179
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,039
Cryonics is a process

180
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:28,960
that preserves bodies of living things.

181
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:35,879
This was the way to keep her.
We must keep her.

182
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:41,320
[Matrix in English] After my dad noticed

183
00:16:41,399 --> 00:16:46,080
that the cancer was growing way faster

184
00:16:46,159 --> 00:16:50,480
and Einz
wouldn't probably be able to fight back,

185
00:16:51,159 --> 00:16:57,279
he said that she might need to be frozen,
and then we're all like, "What?"

186
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:03,480
My auntie, my mother,
everyone was against it.

187
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,440
[in Thai] When everyone learned
about cryonics,

188
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:11,039
her grandparents wondered,
"Why we would do this? What is it?

189
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:12,799
That death is death.

190
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,160
What was the point of doing this?"

191
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:20,039
Can we stop the process of dying? Yes.

192
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:25,920
Can you believe that we can stop it?
This is what I have to show my family.

193
00:17:29,079 --> 00:17:31,079
[indistinct chatter]

194
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:42,880
They asked, "Even if we can preserve her,
has anyone been brought back to life?"

195
00:17:45,079 --> 00:17:46,880
[Nareerat speaking indistinctly]

196
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:52,799
[Sahatorn] Growing up in
an Asian family...

197
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,319
I believe we have souls.

198
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,680
There was conflict within me about that.

199
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:05,279
I do believe that our souls can be reborn.

200
00:18:06,759 --> 00:18:08,920
But we all still disagreed
with one another.

201
00:18:11,559 --> 00:18:14,079
[Nareerat] He said he wanted to give her

202
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:18,839
a chance at a life in the future.

203
00:18:23,119 --> 00:18:26,960
[Sahatorn] I know in my heart
that she can be preserved.

204
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,559
[Nareerat] The way my husband told me...

205
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,680
showed clearly

206
00:18:33,759 --> 00:18:37,960
that he was doing this
out of love for his daughter.

207
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:44,960
[Sahatorn] I spent many months trying
to persuade my wife until she agreed.

208
00:18:45,839 --> 00:18:52,359
She said we could do this,
not because it might or might not work...

209
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:58,359
but we'd do it because I asked to.

210
00:18:59,839 --> 00:19:06,519
The one thing that helped
even those who have no knowledge

211
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:10,839
of the technology to understand us
is our love for her.

212
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:41,039
He knew well
from looking at the medical reports.

213
00:19:41,119 --> 00:19:43,759
We knew in our hearts
that she would pass away.

214
00:19:45,599 --> 00:19:48,240
She'd gone as far as humanly possible.

215
00:19:48,319 --> 00:19:51,960
The doctors admitted
that she would not survive.

216
00:19:59,079 --> 00:20:02,359
PEDIATRICS 2

217
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:04,519
[Sahatorn] We have reached the end.

218
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,720
The end of what's medically,
humanly possible.

219
00:20:09,559 --> 00:20:14,799
There's no more.
We have reached the limit.

220
00:20:16,279 --> 00:20:21,680
[Nareerat] You are in our hearts, always.

221
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:29,119
[Sahatorn] If one day,
you wake up and watch this video,

222
00:20:29,839 --> 00:20:31,799
maybe many hundreds of years from now,

223
00:20:32,519 --> 00:20:36,200
we want you to know we love you.

224
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:56,400
[Nareerat] On her last day,
we were with her.

225
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:59,480
Everyone in our family was with her.

226
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,839
We asked for Einz to die at home.

227
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:06,920
We prayed over her
and told her we loved her.

228
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,359
And prayed that we will see her again.

229
00:21:13,559 --> 00:21:18,000
[woman 1] Dear all beings, our friends
in sin who are born, age, suffer and die.

230
00:21:18,079 --> 00:21:23,319
May you find contentment.
May you find contentment.

231
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,720
May there be no bad fate.

232
00:21:27,039 --> 00:21:31,599
May you find contentment,
have no pain in your body and your heart.

233
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:37,200
May you be content in body and mind.
Take care of your mind and soul.

234
00:21:37,279 --> 00:21:41,640
Find contentment in both.
Forever and beyond.

235
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:45,440
[woman 2] May you find so much happiness.

236
00:21:47,519 --> 00:21:49,960
-[woman 1] You can go now, little fighter.
-[woman 2 sniffles]

